title: Democratic Party (United States) - Wikipedia
snippet: The Democratic Party is a liberal political party in the United States. Sitting on the center to center-left of the political spectrum, it is the world's oldest active political party, having been founded in 1828.

title: History of the Democratic Party (United States) - Wikipedia
snippet: The Democratic Party is one of the two major political parties of the United States political system and the oldest active political party in the country. Founded in 1828, the Democratic Party is the oldest active voter-based political party in the world. The party has changed significantly during its nearly two centuries of existence.

title: Who founded the Democratic Party and the Republican Party, and when were they founded? Why is there no American political party called 'the Liberal Party'? - Quora
